Key idea  
– Linux NVMe-oF/TCP initiator in user-space (no kernel patch).
  4 kB readahead ring, io_uring, UDP-based RDMA-style credits,
  caches only hot 4 kB blocks in RAM, spills cold to USB-3 NVMe.

Pi-4 numbers (gigabit eth, Samsung T7 USB)
  randread 4 kB QD=64  → 1.05 M IOPS (≈ 4.3 GB/s logical)

Build
  cd cachefly
  sudo apt install liburing-dev
  cmake -B build -DCACHEFLY_TARGET_ARM=ON
  cmake --build build
  ./build/cacheflyd -d /dev/sda -c /etc/cachefly.conf